h2. First-Time Installation

There are several ways to install <span class="keyword">Aquarium</span>.

h3. Rubygems

This is the preferred approach. Non-windows users may have to use sudo for each command. Install or update to the latest with:

<pre>
gem install aquarium
gem update aquarium
</pre>  

or if you want an older version:

<pre>
gem install aquarium -v 0.1.0
gem update aquarium -v 0.1.0
</pre>  

h4. Notes on Updating

There are one API incompatibility between version 0.1.5 and 0.1.0. Because of incompatibilities with Rails, requiring the top-level <code>aquarium.rb</code> no longer adds methods to Object. Instead, if you want the convenience ("DSL") methods on Object or on a particular class, you have to include <code>Aquarium::Aspects::DSL::AspectDSL</code>. See "Changes":changes.html for details.

h3. Direct download

Get it from "Rubyforge":http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=4281

h3. Subversion

Check it out:

<pre>
svn checkout svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/aquarium/trunk aquarium_trunk
</pre>

or

<pre>
svn checkout svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/aquarium/tags/{svn_tag: }/aquarium aquarium_{svn_tag: }
</pre>

See the "README":rdoc/files/README.html for details about how to build <span class="keyword">Aquarium</span>.